<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    <title>CheckPoint</title>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11"/>
    <p><img encrypturl="no" src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/Pictures/BK19.png" alt="p1a" texwrap="none" align="top"/></p><br/> 
A block is suspended from a string attached to the ceiling of an elevator. The diagram below shows the forces acting on the block, drawn to scale.

    <part loncapaid="12">
      
        <p>Part 1. The upward and the downward forces, shown in the diagram, are, respectively: </p>
      
      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="no" loncapaid="13" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice name="foil1" correct="false">

                Normal force and tension
            
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil2" correct="false">

                Normal force and gravitational force
            
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil3" correct="false">

                Tension and normal force
            
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil4" correct="true">

                Tension and gravitational force
            
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil5" correct="false">

                Gravitational force and tension.
            
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>
    </part>
    <part loncapaid="14">
      
        <p>Part 2. In which scenario(s) is it possible for the forces to have the magnitudes shown in the diagram? Check all possible answers.</p>
      
      <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" max="10" randomize="yes" loncapaid="15">
        <ul>
          <li>
            
              <p>The elevator is moving upward with a constant speed</p>
            
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil1" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>The elevator is moving downward with a constant speed</p>
            
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil2" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>The elevator is moving downward with increasing speed</p>
            
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil3" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>The elevator is moving downward with decreasing speed</p>
            
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil4" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>The elevator is moving upward with increasing speed</p>
            
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil5" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>The elevator is moving upward with decreasing speed</p>
            
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil6" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>The elevator remains at rest</p>
            
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil7" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </optionresponse>
    </part>
      </problem>
</html>
